  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Midterm Exam">
  <data key="d0">Midterm Exam</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The midterm exam for the course is scheduled for Week 8 (March 6) and accounts for 15% of the final grade.&lt;SEP&gt;An in-class exam worth 30% of the final grade, scheduled for Thursday, 2/26.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb1296e293d05dc37ed35c31463ee77a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfd68ceb87515331e129a9abd37822bd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774689607</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Homework">
  <data key="d0">Homework</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Homework assignments contribute 18% to the final grade and are subject to the course-specific late work policy.&lt;SEP&gt;Academic assignments given to students, subject to strict policies regarding collaboration and external resources.&lt;SEP&gt;Homework is an assignment type, with 4 submissions contributing 40% to the final grade.&lt;SEP&gt;Essay-style assignments requiring the use of the LaTeX typesetting system, contributing 30% to the final grade.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb1296e293d05dc37ed35c31463ee77a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85e73277ca89ae4ac31f7aac9cea80ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f51e6db05ae81233302de58292225c20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfd68ceb87515331e129a9abd37822bd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774689607</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Projects">
  <data key="d0">Projects</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Project assignments contribute 37% to the final grade and are subject to the course-specific late work policy.&lt;SEP&gt;Course activities that involve programming and contribute to the final grade.&lt;SEP&gt;Projects are submissions that require proper disclosure and will not be considered if they cause actual harm.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb1296e293d05dc37ed35c31463ee77a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e27010976757e22b45233a9e6414493&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bde5d5633adc89787a671288bb72ae7c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774690943</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Exams">
  <data key="d0">Exams</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Exams are a method of assessment taken in-class.&lt;SEP&gt;Academic assessments with strict rules on allowed resources and conduct.&lt;SEP&gt;A major component of the final grade, comprising a midterm and a final exam, collectively worth 60%.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb1296e293d05dc37ed35c31463ee77a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85e73277ca89ae4ac31f7aac9cea80ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfd68ceb87515331e129a9abd37822bd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774689607</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Grading Scale">
  <data key="d0">Grading Scale</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The grading scale defines letter grades based on percentage scores: A = 90-100%, B = 70-89%, C = 60-69%, F&lt;SEP&gt;A predefined range of percentages (e.g., A: 90 and above) used to assign final letter grades.&lt;SEP&gt;The Grading Scale defines the letter grades corresponding to percentage scores in the course.&lt;SEP&gt;The system used to convert numerical scores into letter grades (e.g., A, B, C, D, F).</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb1296e293d05dc37ed35c31463ee77a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfd68ceb87515331e129a9abd37822bd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac85e755a4a23edecfe21ce4345b7c3a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f6459a98ec2442f228c8ad996357aaa</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774690109</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
