<node id="Grading Policy">
  <data key="d0">Grading Policy</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Grading Policy outlines the criteria and weight distribution for student grades.&lt;SEP&gt;Grading Policy outlines the rules and procedures for challenging grades and the audit process.&lt;SEP&gt;The established rules for evaluating student performance in the course.&lt;SEP&gt;The Grading Policy outlines how student performance will be evaluated in the course.&lt;SEP&gt;The policy outlining how student grades are calculated and assigned, based on a 10-point scale.&lt;SEP&gt;A set of rules defining how student performance will be evaluated and converted into grades.&lt;SEP&gt;The overall rules and methods used to determine grades in the course, providing flexibility for missed lectures and poor grades.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f51e6db05ae81233302de58292225c20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-686108f24ad2964e2eb6746fc5d77479&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f6459a98ec2442f228c8ad996357aaa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6994146b2ef6c66515740ca859a8ce5c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d4d7a435627d3123be862f9617801d3d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-afae5217c3b2c566e8895a2a66b34822&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ab0d5c1bcca720fccfe2829382925b70</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774690817</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Midterms">
  <data key="d0">Midterms</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Midterms are closed-book assessments, with 3 midterms contributing 45% to the final grade.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f51e6db05ae81233302de58292225c20</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774689405</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Quizzes">
  <data key="d0">Quizzes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Quizzes are closed-book assessments, with 3 quizzes contributing 15% to the final grade.&lt;SEP&gt;Online or in-class assessments consisting of a few simple questions, contributing 10% to the final grade.&lt;SEP&gt;Quizzes are assessments that can be included in Pre-Class Engagement.&lt;SEP&gt;Quizzes represent a category of graded work contributing 40% to the final grade in the course.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f51e6db05ae81233302de58292225c20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfd68ceb87515331e129a9abd37822bd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-686108f24ad2964e2eb6746fc5d77479&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac85e755a4a23edecfe21ce4345b7c3a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774690041</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Late Work Policy">
  <data key="d0">Late Work Policy</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Late Work Policy is a comprehensive set of rules and guidelines that governs the submission of academic assignments after their designated due date or deadline. This policy outlines general procedures for accepting late submissions of academic work, with a specific focus on assignments submitted after the deadline. It also details provisions for specific exemptions, particularly regarding makeup work for excused absences, for which general guidelines are provided. In certain contexts, this policy is further detailed, for instance, within frameworks such as Student Rule 7.&lt;SEP&gt;A policy that deducts 10% for each late day from submissions, with a 0 grade assigned after three days past the deadline.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f51e6db05ae81233302de58292225c20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6c491839f19e2ead354056f60e29d9f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfd68ceb87515331e129a9abd37822bd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-01325762279bde457b25b8a2357fe587&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8dc1a310c66edf47b8a102834996fffe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac85e755a4a23edecfe21ce4345b7c3a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f6459a98ec2442f228c8ad996357aaa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b5221657b3f1d03b70bf0dc540651a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0e61c7d052ddb26fad7475ce76968aeb</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774690665</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Course Specific Late Work Policy">
  <data key="d0">Course Specific Late Work Policy</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Course Specific Late Work Policy establishes a set of guidelines and rules specifically for a particular course, detailing the procedures and consequences for submitting assignments, homework, and project components after their original deadlines. This policy outlines various penalties for late submissions and may specify conditions under which exceptions can be made. It often mandates that all assignments must be submitted through a designated platform, such as Canvas, explicitly stating that late or email submissions will not be accepted. The policy can also indicate that no late assignments will be accepted after a set deadline, while some versions may incorporate details regarding "granted late days." Furthermore, this policy can be referenced by a broader makeup work policy and, in certain contexts, may mention that even on-time work is eligible for partial credit.&lt;SEP&gt;A policy detailing rules for late homework submissions, including the allocation of five late days and the consequence of a grade of 0 after using them.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f51e6db05ae81233302de58292225c20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6c491839f19e2ead354056f60e29d9f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfd68ceb87515331e129a9abd37822bd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-01325762279bde457b25b8a2357fe587&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-15e36cbcbf082773e37b1a2738feea98&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8dc1a310c66edf47b8a102834996fffe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac85e755a4a23edecfe21ce4345b7c3a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f6459a98ec2442f228c8ad996357aaa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b5221657b3f1d03b70bf0dc540651a1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774690365</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Student Rule 7">
  <data key="d0">Student Rule 7</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Student Rule 7 is a specific university rule that primarily governs makeup work for excused absences. This rule is consistently referenced within the Late Work Policy. Its fundamental purpose is to exempt makeup work necessitated by an excused absence from the stipulations of the general late work policy. Furthermore, Student Rule 7 defines what constitutes an excused absence and outlines the associated policies for students regarding such situations.&lt;SEP&gt;A rule referenced in the policy regarding makeup work for excused absences.&lt;SEP&gt;A specific university regulation that outlines policies regarding excused absences and exemptions from the late work policy.&lt;SEP&gt;A specific rule or guideline referenced for determining if a situation is covered for an excused absence and for outlining submission timelines.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f51e6db05ae81233302de58292225c20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6c491839f19e2ead354056f60e29d9f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bfd68ceb87515331e129a9abd37822bd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-01325762279bde457b25b8a2357fe587&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8dc1a310c66edf47b8a102834996fffe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac85e755a4a23edecfe21ce4345b7c3a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f6459a98ec2442f228c8ad996357aaa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b5221657b3f1d03b70bf0dc540651a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0e61c7d052ddb26fad7475ce76968aeb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fbe6bf9cd527c6fbb62c72752b72aed0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ab0d5c1bcca720fccfe2829382925b70</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774690816</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Course Schedule">
  <data key="d0">Course Schedule</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Course Schedule provides an overview of lecture topics, titles, and assignment due dates throughout the semester.&lt;SEP&gt;A section outlining the weekly plan and topics for the course.&lt;SEP&gt;A section outlining the course's modules, assignment due dates, and exam dates.&lt;SEP&gt;The Course Schedule is a document outlining the topics for each week and the due dates for assignments over 15 weeks.&lt;SEP&gt;A rough, subject-to-change outline of the topics and activities planned for each week of the course.&lt;SEP&gt;A detailed outline of topics, dates, and due items for the course across 16 weeks.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f51e6db05ae81233302de58292225c20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e37fa109ec92fd9441dfefb914b096&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8dc1a310c66edf47b8a102834996fffe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7202137a45abe2684738a25443ea1cee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b5221657b3f1d03b70bf0dc540651a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0e61c7d052ddb26fad7475ce76968aeb</data>
